values:
&nbsp;Another year, another Christmas, come and gone. Without my brother, Mike, I cannot say this was the best Christmas ever, but it was pretty darn good. Several cute new tops (mainly stuff I can wear to work AND out and about), a Russian composer (a CD...not the composer himself as that's just awkward), and a Monet calendar were nice, but the real treasures were, of course, the BBC DVD's, which were as follows this year: Doctor Who Series 3 and "A Holy Wholly Happy Ending" aka the series finale of the Vicar of Dibley with, you guessed it, Richard Armitage as the vicar's love interest.&nbsp;

Needless to say, my last few hours of Christmas were spent watching Blackadder's Christmas Carol with my cousins (as tradition and our love of Blackadder dictate) and RA being all cute and adorable and not the villain. Glorious.&nbsp;

And the giant Christmas Eve party didn't go so bad either. I mean, I was largely ignored by all my relatives, so I mostly avoided all their pitiful looks of "Oh, she still hasn't found a full time job."

Speaking of, here I sit, at another temp job doing reception. I dread my first phone call...it's not that I can't handle answering phones or something...I just fear dropping a call or something...oh wait...just got one and I think I may have dropped it (DAMN IT!). &nbsp;Anywho, receptionist also means sitting around all day...probably putzing around online (awww shucks...isn't that what I do at home anyway?) and reading Dostoevsky when I need a break...because lazy git that I am I've been reading The Idiot for the past five months!&nbsp;

Other news, while the holidays are my favorite time of year, I'm very excited they are pretty much over, as I'm sick of my ovaries acting up and prompting me to want a man. Perhaps I will dwell less on He Who Is Toxic and go back to feeling the way I did before November (happy to be rid of him and not occasionally...very occasionally and not at length at all...talking to him).

Well, Cheerie-Bye!

One of the few joys&nbsp;I have had lately is discovering that I can watch episodes of&nbsp;the new&nbsp;series of Robin Hood on youtube... 

And now they've taken it away from me! My hope, which I will find out next Sunday or Monday, is that people will continue to post the episodes, and&nbsp;I'll get a chance to watch the good bits. Granted, I don't watch whole episodes (I want to save something for our Saturday night&nbsp;Richard Fests), but it just made me happy to know that they were there, and I was able to watch the new season and not wait until MARCH!&nbsp; 

*starts&nbsp;searching for jobs in the UK*&nbsp; 

Cheerie-Bye.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
***EDIT***

No, really, there are a ton of great editing jobs in the UK (one of them was in Stirling, Scotland *dies*).

&nbsp;Tim Kring - If you kill HRG, I will do something crazy - like send you a ticking pipe bomb that forces you to sing and dance along with its rhythm until it ultimately blows you up!&nbsp;

Or just write you lots of hate mail. And I mean LOTS!

P.S.
If you do do the unthinkable, you can make up for it by sending me Adrian Pasdar, avec or sans gnarly beard.&nbsp;

Cheerie-Bye.
